Quoting Jon Hanna jon@hackcraft.net : From http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/struct/lists.html : "Another application of DL, for example, is for marking up dialogues, with each DT naming a speaker, and each DD containing his or her words." 
That clearly isn't a matter of terms and descriptions, so I think it justifies the use of dl for general name/value pairs. 
I'm now happy again that this isn't HTML abuse, and indeed is quite appropriate. 
